Our Environmental Data Center (EDC) operates in multiple monitoring environments across Japan. These include domestic, industrial, urban, and volcanic areas. We continuously monitor over 30 parameters, including carbon dioxide (CO₂), carbon monoxide (CO), nitrogen dioxide (NO₂), sulfur dioxide (SO₂), ozone (O₃), particulate matter (PM1.0, PM2.5, and PM10), volatile organic compounds (VOC), hydrogen sulfide (H₂S), and noise level (dB). 

Please review the following data summary:

- Location type: {{environment_type}}
- Air temperature (°C): {{air_temperature}}
- Air humidity (%): {{air_humidity}}
- Atmospheric pressure (hPa): {{air_pressure}}
- Carbon dioxide (CO₂ ppm): {{co2}}
- Carbon monoxide (CO ppm): {{co}}
- Nitrogen dioxide (NO₂ ppm): {{no2}}
- Sulfur dioxide (SO₂ ppm): {{so2}}
- Ozone (O₃ ppm): {{o3}}
- Particulate matter PM1.0 (µg/m³): {{pm1}}
- Particulate matter PM2.5 (µg/m³): {{pm25}}
- Particulate matter PM10 (µg/m³): {{pm10}}
- Volatile organic compounds (VOC ppm): {{voc}}
- Hydrogen sulfide (H₂S ppm): {{h2s}}
- Noise level (dB): {{noise_level}}
- Ambient light (lux): {{ambient_light}}
